President Obama has declared a major disaster in South Dakota due to flooding that occurred from March 11, 2011, onwards. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures in various counties throughout the state. Mark A. Neveau has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on additional damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.